      %article.intro
        .inner
          %h2 Product Design
          %p
            Successful product design results in products and solutions that are
            useful, usable and desirable and drive business sustainability. I
            aim to achieve this by using design thinking, the combination of
            empathy, creativity and rationality, to understand and solve
            problems in a human centered way.
          %p
            A product development process that is driven by design thinking can be broken into three phases:
          %ol
            %li
              %p
                %strong Understanding the problem,
                %span
                  the people with the problem and the situation in which they
                  experience the problem so that we are enabled to create
                  powerful solutions.
            %li
              %p
                %strong Generating a large diversity of solution concepts
                %span
                  to uncover opportunities that we may have otherwise never
                  discovered or considered.
            %li
              %p
                %strong Qualitatively and quantitatively testing ideas
                %span
                  so that we can confidently focus on refining and implementing
                  the most appropriate and viable solution.
          %p
            A product design process that internalizes design
            thinking is a core driver of innovation and a defensible business
            strategy.

      %article.examples
